    "explanation": "<p>The general name of the compound formed by the reaction between aldehyde and alcohol is acetal. e.g.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1ltc5dyvq/628ba5c9-ce83-4a0a-b398-d53d7cd22d90/5dd94760-d9b6-11ee-983a-35ba8017a6a3/file-6y3zli1ltc5dyvr.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1ltc5dyvq/628ba5c9-ce83-4a0a-b398-d53d7cd22d90/5dd94760-d9b6-11ee-983a-35ba8017a6a3/file-6y3zli1ltc5dyvr.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2022 Chemistry - Aldehyde and Ketone Question 16 English Explanation\"></p>",
