  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The test to differentiate between pentan-2-one and pentan-3-one is</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "Benedict's test\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "Fehling's test\n\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "Iodoform test"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "Baeyer's test"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Pentan-2-one gives positive iodoform test when react with $$\\mathrm{NaOH}$$ and $$\\mathrm{I}_2$$ and form yellow precipitates of iodoform. While pentan-3-one does not gives positive iodoform test. The involved reactions given below :</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1ltc5lq92/2c0b8fd0-7042-42a7-b69f-8ad4cf45ea82/35a7dc60-d9b7-11ee-983a-35ba8017a6a3/file-6y3zli1ltc5lq93.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1ltc5lq92/2c0b8fd0-7042-42a7-b69f-8ad4cf45ea82/35a7dc60-d9b7-11ee-983a-35ba8017a6a3/file-6y3zli1ltc5lq93.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2022 Chemistry - Aldehyde and Ketone Question 17 English Explanation\"></p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2022",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>An organic compound $$X$$ on treatment with PCC in dichloromethane gives the compound $$Y$$. Compound $$Y$$ reacts with $$\\mathrm{I}_2$$ and alkali to form yellow precipitate of triiodomethane. The compound $$X$$ is</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "$$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO}$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "$$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COCH}_3$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "$$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{OH}$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "$$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COOH}$$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Compound (Y) gives iodoform test, that means it contains acetyl group <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltbf5qtw/30bb2acd-ae2c-4e0e-879c-cb3f1efad5aa/cbcc6d40-d94f-11ee-9419-570707b09c32/file-1ltbf5qtx.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltbf5qtw/30bb2acd-ae2c-4e0e-879c-cb3f1efad5aa/cbcc6d40-d94f-11ee-9419-570707b09c32/file-1ltbf5qtx.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2021 Chemistry - Aldehyde and Ketone Question 13 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>PCC is an oxidising agent which oxidised the alcohol to aldehyde or ketone (depends upon the reactant alcohol). That means $$X$$ is an alcohol.</p>\n<p>From the given information, it is concluded that the compound $$X$$ is an alcohol (which contain two carbon). Thus, the alcohol is $$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{OH}$$.</p>\n<p>The reaction involves are as follows :</p>\n<p>$$\\mathrm{\\mathop {C{H_3}C{H_2}OH}\\limits_{(X)} \\mathrel{\\mathop{\\kern0pt\\longrightarrow}\n\\limits_{C{H_2}C{l_2}}^{PCC}} \\mathop {C{H_3}CHO}\\limits_{(Y)} \\mathrel{\\mathop{\\kern0pt\\longrightarrow}\n\\limits_{NaOH}^{{I_2}}} CH{I_3} + HCO\\mathop O\\limits^ -  \\mathop N\\limits^ +  a}$$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2021,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2021",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltbgn8b5/52acb714-c8fb-4250-83b5-f2f574bd5552/9b2f7410-d955-11ee-bc73-1359a1a033ae/file-1ltbgn8b6.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltbgn8b5/52acb714-c8fb-4250-83b5-f2f574bd5552/9b2f7410-d955-11ee-bc73-1359a1a033ae/file-1ltbgn8b6.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2021 Chemistry - Aldehyde and Ketone Question 14 English\"></p>\n<p>$$A, B$$ and $$C$$ respectively are</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "ethanol, ethane nitrile and ethyne\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "ethane nitrile, ethanol and ethyne\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "ethyne, ethanol and ethane nitrile\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "ethyne, ethane nitrile and ethanol"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Ethyne on reaction with $$\\mathrm{HgSO}_4 / \\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{SO}_4$$ gives ethanol (i.e. $$\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}-\\mathrm{OH}$$) which interconvert (i.e. tautomerises) to give acetaldehyde $$(\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO})$$.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltbgpr0y/d534f383-4d34-41a6-915f-11f05a3c858c/e1430f20-d955-11ee-bc73-1359a1a033ae/file-1ltbgpr0z.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltbgpr0y/d534f383-4d34-41a6-915f-11f05a3c858c/e1430f20-d955-11ee-bc73-1359a1a033ae/file-1ltbgpr0z.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2021 Chemistry - Aldehyde and Ketone Question 14 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>PCC is an oxidising agent, which oxidised the alcohol to aldehyde. Therefore, $$(B)$$ is an alcohol, i.e. ethanol.</p>\n<p>$$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{OH} \\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{PCC}} \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO}$$</p>\n<p>Ethane nitrile on reaction with $$\\mathrm{SnCl}_2 / \\mathrm{HCl}$$ followed by acid hydrolysis give acetaldehyde.</p>\n<p>$$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CN} \\xrightarrow[\\text { (ii) } \\mathrm{H}_3 \\mathrm{O}^{+}]{\\text {(i) } \\mathrm{SnCl}_2 / \\mathrm{HCl}} \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO}$$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2021,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2021",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO} \\xrightarrow[\\text { (ii) } \\mathrm{H}_3 \\mathrm{O}^{+}]{\\text {(i) } \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{MgBr}} A \\xrightarrow[\\Delta]{\\text { Conc. } \\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{SO}_4} \\\\\n& B \\xrightarrow[\\text { (ii) } \\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}, \\mathrm{OH}^{-}]{\\text {(i) } \\mathrm{B}_2 \\mathrm{H}_6} C \\\\\n&\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>\n<p>$$A$$ and $$C$$ are</p>",
