    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The complete given reaction is as follows</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltbha0l9/77bc0606-098a-47e4-b490-c33317d17259/14d532d0-d958-11ee-bc73-1359a1a033ae/file-1ltbha0la.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltbha0l9/77bc0606-098a-47e4-b490-c33317d17259/14d532d0-d958-11ee-bc73-1359a1a033ae/file-1ltbha0la.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2021 Chemistry - Aldehyde and Ketone Question 15 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>In compounds $$(A)$$ and $$(C)$$ only the position of $$-\\mathrm{OH}$$ group is changed. Thus, compounds $$A$$ and $$C$$ are position isomers.</p>",
