    "explanation": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lth60vwl/d7fe8b32-9e8b-43db-9516-515bd4ec18b5/c6683b50-dc78-11ee-ae06-d5d53a247af4/file-1lth60vwm.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lth60vwl/d7fe8b32-9e8b-43db-9516-515bd4ec18b5/c6683b50-dc78-11ee-ae06-d5d53a247af4/file-1lth60vwm.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2020 Chemistry - Aldehyde and Ketone Question 11 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Here, aldol condensation reaction is taking place.</p>",
