  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "Which of the following compounds undergoes haloform reaction?\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COCH}_3$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "$$\n\\text {  } \\mathrm{HCHO}\n$$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{Br}$\n\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "$\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{O}-\\mathrm{CH}_3$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The haloform reaction occurs when a compound contains a methyl ketone group ($\\mathrm{CH}_3\\text{COR}$) or converts into one during the reaction. Here’s a quick breakdown of each option:</p>\n\n<p>$$\\mathrm{CH}_3\\mathrm{COCH}_3$$  </p>\n\n\n<p><p>This is acetone, which is a methyl ketone. It has a $\\mathrm{CH}_3$ group directly connected to the carbonyl group.  </p></p>\n<p><p>Under basic conditions with a halogen, the methyl group is transformed into a trihalomethyl group, which is then cleaved off as a haloform.  </p></p>\n<p><p>Thus, acetone undergoes the haloform reaction.</p></p>\n\n\n<p>$$\\mathrm{HCHO}$$  </p>\n\n\n<p><p>This is formaldehyde. It lacks the necessary $\\mathrm{CH}_3$ group adjacent to the carbonyl (in fact, it doesn’t have a methyl group at all).  </p></p>\n<p><p>Therefore, it does not undergo the haloform reaction.</p></p>\n\n\n<p>$$\\mathrm{CH}_3\\mathrm{CH}_2\\mathrm{Br}$$  </p>\n\n\n<p><p>This compound is bromoethane, an alkyl halide without a carbonyl group.  </p></p>\n<p><p>It does not have the structure required for the haloform reaction.</p></p>\n\n\n<p>$$\\mathrm{CH}_3\\text{-O-}\\mathrm{CH}_3$$  </p>\n\n\n<p><p>This is dimethyl ether, which is an ether and not a ketone.  </p></p>\n<p><p>It does not undergo the haloform reaction.</p></p>\n\n<p>Based on this analysis, the only compound that undergoes the haloform reaction is:</p>\n<p>$$\\text{Option A: } \\mathrm{CH}_3\\mathrm{COCH}_3.$$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2018,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2018",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "The appropriate reagent for the following ransformation is\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7gc3bya/f16a426a-fdaa-4594-9484-9eb06d59f6a8/bfda0220-f12e-11ef-bb55-99fd8798b104/file-jaoe38c1m7gc3byb.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7gc3bya/f16a426a-fdaa-4594-9484-9eb06d59f6a8/bfda0220-f12e-11ef-bb55-99fd8798b104/file-jaoe38c1m7gc3byb.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2018 Chemistry - Aldehyde and Ketone Question 6 English\">",
