      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "$\\mathrm{NaBH}_4$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<ol start=\"\">\n<p>The given reaction is an example of Wolff-Kishner reaction in which aldehyde/ketone group reduce to alkane $\\left(-\\mathrm{CH}_2\\right)$ in the presence of $\\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{~N}-\\mathrm{NH}_2, \\mathrm{KOH} /$ ethylene glycol.</p>\n\n<p>$\\therefore$ (b) is the correct option.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2018,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2018",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
