    "explanation": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7hmnf05/09ce1e86-40ac-46a6-992c-a0d25040944e/d2552e50-f1e4-11ef-aab0-892656acd133/file-jaoe38c1m7hmnf06.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7hmnf05/09ce1e86-40ac-46a6-992c-a0d25040944e/d2552e50-f1e4-11ef-aab0-892656acd133/file-jaoe38c1m7hmnf06.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2018 Chemistry - Aldehyde and Ketone Question 5 English Explanation\">\n<p>$$\\text { (This reaction is Etard reaction) }$$</p>\n<p>$$ \\text { In this reaction } Z \\text { is benzaldehyde. } $$</p>",
